description: Number of multisets of n positive integers with equal sum and product.
comments: The multiset {n^1, 2^1, 1^(n-2)} has n elements and sum = product = 2n. Hence a(n) >= 1.
references: R. K. Guy, 'Unsolved Problems in Number Theory' (Section D24).
links: David Radcliffe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000
author: _David W. Wilson_
